3_1_7.Solution:
7. The correct answer is $\mathrm{B}$. The density of a solution can be determined from $\rho=m / V$, where $\rho$ is the density of the solution (in units of $\mathrm{g} / \mathrm{cm}^{3}$ ), $m$ is the mass of the solution (in units of $\mathrm{g}$ ), and $V$ is the volume of the solution (in units of $\mathrm{cm}^{3}$ ). The mass of the solution, $m_{\text {sol }}$, is the total mass of the solution and the syringe, $m_{\text {tot }}$, minus the mass of the syringe, $m_{\mathrm{syr}}$, or

$$
\begin{aligned}
& m_{\mathrm{tot}}=m_{\mathrm{sol}}+m_{\mathrm{syr}} \\
& m_{\mathrm{sol}}=m_{\mathrm{tot}}-m_{\mathrm{syr}}=80 \mathrm{~g}-5 \mathrm{~g}=75 \mathrm{~g}
\end{aligned}
$$

The volume of the solution in the syringe is $V_{\mathrm{syr}}=30 \mathrm{~mL}=30 \mathrm{~cm}^{3}$. The density of the solution is:

$$
\rho=\frac{m}{V}=\frac{75 \mathrm{~g}}{30 \mathrm{~cm}^{3}}=2.5 \frac{\mathrm{g}}{\mathrm{cm}^{3}}
$$

